latestIgtvVideos.caption:
#ForTheLoveOf
One year ago, I was facing severe sensitivity problem and For sensitivity relief, and effective cleaning of my teeth and gums, I was recommended twice daily brushing with Sensodyne toothpaste with fluoride using a soft bristled toothbrush by my dentist.
As soon as my tooth sensitivity got recovered I decided to take a 3 days trip to Mundota Palace and Fort in Jaipur.
Food is the only thing I look up to when I plan a trip to Jaipur. I was very happy because now I don't have any sensitivity problem.

I was mesmerized by the sheer beauty of the Palace and it's natural surroundings. I was excited for this trip because I was going to have Rajasthani food prepared by known Chef of that city.
During my trip to Jaipur I had Dal baati , Churma which is an Indian dish of dal and baati. It is popular in Rajasthan. Dal is prepared using tuvaar dal, chana dal, mung dal, moth dal, or urad dal.
I also had Palak Paneer, Aloo Puri, Dal, Chole ,Upma, Seviyan, Mutton, Gulab Jamun.
Earlier I can't even imagine of having all my favorite food due to my sensitivity problem and now I am enjoying every occasion of my life by having my favorite food. All thanks to Sensodyne toothpaste & Brush 🥰

💛My ŠKODA Superstar Story: From Delhi to Mumbai with Daisy💛

I’m Suruchi Mehta, a dreamer, part-time accountant, and aspiring TV serial actress, with my 10-year-old Labrador retriever, Daisy, as my constant companion. Moving from Delhi to Mumbai to chase my acting dreams was a bold leap, fueled by ŠKODA’s “Simply Clever” spirit and my trusty ŠKODA Superb. For Daisy and me, love is taking the longer route, because we treasure the ride.

Leaving Delhi’s stability—my accounting job, our flat, and family—was daunting. Mumbai, the heart of Indian TV, beckoned, but finding a pet-friendly rental was a struggle. Landlords rejected us, leaving Daisy and me in cramped flats or budget hotels, her presence calming my doubts. Our ŠKODA Superb was our heaven. Driving 1,000 kilometers to Mumbai, Daisy lounged in the spacious back seat, the Superb’s 5-star safety and smooth TGDI engine making the scenic Rajasthan route a joy—windows down, music on, pure freedom.

Mumbai’s chaos—monsoons, traffic, auditions from Malad to Versova—tested me. Balancing accounting and acting was grueling. Early rejections stung, and savings dwindled. A major role clashed with a critical audit, pushing me to my limit. But Daisy and I escaped in the Superb to Lonavala’s hills, its reliability mirroring her loyalty. Those drives recharged me. Persistence paid off—a recurring role, then a continuity role in a serial. The audience’s love and my family’s pride made every hardship worthwhile.

With a pet-friendly Andheri flat, my careers thrive—bigger roles, high-stakes accounts. Daisy joins me in the Superb for beach getaways, still sprightly.
